# Lab 05: Azure Storage Automation with PowerShell

## Objectives

By completing this lab, you will:
- [ ] Create a storage account with Zone-Redundant Storage (ZRS)
- [ ] Manage blob containers and upload/download files programmatically
- [ ] Generate and use SAS tokens for secure delegated access
- [ ] Create Azure File shares
- [ ] Implement storage account key rotation best practices

## Prerequisites

- Azure subscription with Contributor or Owner role
- PowerShell 7+ with Az.Storage module installed
- Basic understanding of cloud storage concepts
- Text editor for creating sample files

## Lab Environment

You will create the following resources:
- Resource Group: `lab05-storage-rg`
- Location: `northeurope`
- Storage Account: `lab05sa[random]` (globally unique name)
- Blob Container: `lab-blobs`
- Azure File Share: `lab-files`

